data.chText: 提拔，晋升，提升（到不应有的位置）
data.enText: to give sb/sth a higher position or rank, often more important than they deserve

data.chText: 他将许多朋友都提拔到政府部门的要职上。
data.enText: He elevated many of his friends to powerful positions within the government.

data.chText: 这是试图将足球拔高成一门学科来进行严肃的研究。
data.enText: It was an attempt to elevate football to a subject worthy of serious study.
to lift sth up or put sth in a higher position

data.chText: 将受伤的腿抬高是很重要的。
data.enText: It is important that the injured leg should be elevated.
to make the level of sth increase

data.chText: 使情绪高昂；使精神振奋；使兴高采烈
data.enText: to improve a person's mood, so that they feel happy

data.chText: 这首歌总使他精神振奋。
data.enText: The song never failed to elevate his spirits.

simple_means.memory_skill: e 出 + lev 举起 + ate 表动词 → 举出 → 举起

ex.chText: 吊车把集装箱吊运到卡车上。
ex.enText: The crane lifted the container onto the truck.

ex.chText: 她揭开汤锅的盖子加了些盐。
ex.enText: She lifted the lid on the pot of soup to add some salt.

ex.chText: 这块石头太重了，我搬不起来。
ex.enText: The stone is too heavy for me to lift.
He lifted his hand to knock on the door.

synonyms.bx: 指用体力或机械将人或事物举起；也指抬起某一身体部位。

ex.chText: 把病人慢慢托到直立的位置。
ex.enText: Gradually elevate the patient into an upright position.

ex.chText: 他们企图把罗兰抬上总统宝座。
ex.enText: They attempted to elevate Roland to the position of president.

synonyms.bx: 指将人或物抬高、举高，也可引申指提高地位或职位。

ex.chText: 水手们早晨升起了旗帜。
ex.enText: The sailors hoisted the flags in the morning.

ex.chText: 他们需要吊起混凝土块。
ex.enText: They need to hoist the concrete blocks.

synonyms.bx: 常指用绳索、起重机等把某物升起。

ex.chText: 他把哑铃从地上举起来。
ex.enText: He raised the dumbbell from the ground.

ex.chText: 我举双手赞成拦河筑坝。
ex.enText: I'll raise both hands in favour of damming the river.
He raised his eyes and stared at her.

synonyms.bx: 常指用体力将某事物抬高或举高；也指抬起眼睛、头或脸以向上看。

example: The new law lifted many people from poverty

tr: raise from a lower to a higher position
give a promotion to or assign to a higher position
example: John was kicked upstairs when a replacement was hired
Women tend not to advance in the major law firms
I got promoted after many years of hard work

value.def: When someone or something achieves a more important rank or status, you can say that they are elevated to it.

example.ex: He was elevated to the post of prime minister.
The Prime Minister is known to favour the elevation of more women to the Cabinet...
example.tran: 人所共知首相希望提拔更多女性进入内阁。

example.ex: After his elevation to the papacy, he reigned for two years.
example.tran: 他升任教皇后在位两年。

value.def: If you elevate something to a higher status, you consider it to be better or more important than it really is.

example.ex: Don't elevate your superiors to superstar status.
example.tran: 别把你的上司捧得跟超级巨星似的。

value.def: To elevate something means to increase it in amount or intensity.

example.ex: Emotional stress can elevate blood pressure.
example.tran: 情绪压力可能会导致血压升高。

example.ex: ...overweight individuals who have elevated cholesterol levels.
example.tran: 胆固醇水平升高的体重超标者

value.def: If you elevate something, you raise it above a horizontal level.

example.ex: Jack elevated the gun at the sky.

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to raise, to lighten 提高, 举起；变轻
rootsaffixes.title: lev, liev

partsOfSpeech.dec: al 加强 + levi 提高，举起；变轻 + ate 做，造成，使… → 不断变轻 → 减轻
e 出 + lev 提高，举起；变轻 + ate 做，造成，使… → 举出 → 举起
ir 不 + relevant 相关的 → 不相干的，不切题的
lev 提高，举起；变轻 + ee 与…有关的物 → 提高防洪堤的高度来防洪 → 防洪堤
lev 提高，举起；变轻 + el 地点 → 举到同一高度 → 平的
lev 提高，举起；变轻 + er 表物 → 举起〔重物〕的物 → 杠杆
lev 提高，举起；变轻 + it 走 + ate 使… → 举起某物 → 使升到空中
lev 提高，举起；变轻 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 变轻 → 轻浮
lev 提高，举起；变轻 + y 表行为 → 提高〔政府收入〕→ 征税
re 一再 + lev 提高，举起；变轻 + ant …的 → 一再想提高的 →〔态度〕中肯的
re 一再 + lief〔= liev〕提高，举起；变轻 → 减轻；轻松
re 一再 + liev 提高，举起；变轻 + e → 使再三变轻 → 减轻
